\section{Existence of an Albanese variety}

The classical construction of the Jacobian goes through the Picard scheme machinery: $\Jac(C)$ is the connected component of the identity of $\Pic^0_{C/k}$. An equivalent route, available whenever a $k$-rational point $P \in C(k)$ has been fixed, is to take the Stein factorisation of the Abel--Jacobi morphism $\Sym^g(C) \to \Pic^g_{C/k}$ and translate by $-gP$.

\begin{theorem}[Existence of an Albanese variety for a pointed curve]
  \label{thm:nonempty_jacobianWitness}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.nonempty_jacobianWitness}
  \uses{def:IsAlbanese, def:Jacobian, def:genus}
  Let $C$ be a smooth proper geometrically irreducible curve over a field $k$ and let $P \in C(k)$ be a $k$-rational point. There exists a smooth proper geometrically irreducible group scheme $J$ over $k$ of relative dimension $g(C)$ such that $J$ is an Albanese object for the pointed curve $(C, P)$ in the sense of Definition~\ref{def:IsAlbanese}.
\end{theorem}

\begin{proof}
  \uses{def:IsAlbanese}
  Either of the two classical constructions provides $J$: (i) take $J = \Pic^0_{C/k}$ and pull back along the Abel--Jacobi map sending $P$ to the identity; (ii) form the Stein factorisation of $\Sym^g(C) \to \Pic^g_{C/k}$ translated by $-gP$ and take the connected component of the identity. Both routes yield a smooth proper geometrically irreducible group scheme of dimension $g(C)$ and verify the universal property by the corresponding universal property of $\Pic^0_{C/k}$. Mathlib does not yet contain either Pic-scheme representability nor symmetric powers / quotients of schemes by finite group actions, so the existence statement is recorded here as a working hypothesis backing all downstream consequences.
\end{proof}

\section{Implementation route via the Albanese functor}

Because the full Picard-scheme representability theorem is not available in current Mathlib, the formal construction proceeds in two layers:

\begin{enumerate}
  \item \textbf{Layer I --- direct definition.} The Jacobian of $C$ is defined as an object of the category of $k$-schemes over $\Spec k$ carrying the four properties of Theorems~\ref{thm:Jacobian_grpObj}--\ref{thm:Jacobian_geomIrred}. When the genus is $0$ the underlying scheme is the terminal object $\Spec k$; for higher genus it is the abelian variety provided by Theorem~\ref{thm:nonempty_jacobianWitness}.

  \item \textbf{Layer II --- Abel--Jacobi compatibility.} Chapter~\ref{chap:AbelJacobi} introduces the Abel--Jacobi morphism $C \to \Jac(C)$ and shows that it is universal among morphisms from $C$ to abelian varieties.
\end{enumerate>

