  Existence and uniqueness of the factorisation $g$ are then exactly the universal-property data carried by $\iota_P$ in Definition~\ref{def:IsAlbanese}: for every pointed $f \colon C \to A$ with $f \circ P = \eta_A$, there exists a unique $g \colon J \to A$ with $f = \iota_P \circ g$.

  In the genus-$0$ case, $\Jac(C) = \Spec k$ is the terminal object in the category of $k$-schemes over $\Spec k$, so every morphism into the trivial group scheme is uniquely determined by its source.
